      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is CSS?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to style HTML elements. It controls colors, layouts, spacing, fonts, and overall visual appearance of web pages."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why Use CSS?"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Improve Design** – Add colors, fonts, and layouts",
        "**Separation of Concerns** – Keep structure (HTML) separate from design (CSS)",
        "**Responsive Design** – Make websites work on all devices",
        "**Reusability** – Apply styles across multiple pages"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Ways to Apply CSS"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "value": "1. Inline CSS"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<p style=\"color: red;\">This is red text</p>"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "value": "2. Internal CSS"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<style>\n  p {\n    color: blue;\n  }\n</style>"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "value": "3. External CSS (Recommended)"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"styles.css\">"
    },
